CHAPTER 23 — THE LAST REDOUBT FALLS QUIET / RETURN TO RIFTEN
Session play-log. Picks up on initiative at the Forelhost laboratory freeze;
ends at Balimund's investment. (Riften wrap only partly run — see CARRIED FORWARD.)

=====================================================================
FORELHOST — THE LABORATORY (Section 5), THE FIGHT
=====================================================================
- Opened on initiative at the freeze: trap sprung, Alfonso's body unmade by the
  sterilization field, his soul in the corroded rapier on the cage floor under
  his own Stabilized ice; the extraction arm could not reach it (machine drew
  nothing — Antoine lost his backup sample). False Draugr deploying.

- ISMARA OPENED THE SESSION (Davinia's player late, childcare). By table agreement
  Ismara held the wheel from the START and played the opening ROUND of the fight —
  one-shotting a False Draugr with a special attack (cold/Aegis, doubled). Then the
  player ARRIVED, and the hand-back came with a REVELATION: he glimpsed the ICE PALACE
  Ismara has been building inside Davinia's mind — the integration made visible — before
  taking back control and finishing the fight as Davinia. CDI did NOT advance (cost-free
  loan, ruled a kindness, not a Sovereign's Domain check). PRECEDENT SET: the party has
  now met Ismara as someone who can drive and converse. (This was the LOAN; the EXTENDED
  swap — where Davinia gives in for real — comes below.)

- THE FALSE DRAUGR WERE UNDER-TIERED. Saijah hits ~50 in a single shot vs their 35
  HP, so they were one-shot and the regen/control design never engaged. REBALANCE
  PENDING (logged in GM Guide/False Draugr Reference): bump HP ~60-70 and/or DR, or
  re-pitch as a pure control swarm; tune to the AP~12 party. Party cleared them — but
  ONE Draugr's body stayed INTACT after it dropped (sets up the gas-cloud / the swap below).

- SAIJAH PICKED UP THE RAPIER. Auto-infected on contact (Hircine will burn it out —
  feverish a day, then fine). The borrowed-body link engaged: Alfonso, Wakeful, could
  act through her and speak into her mind. (First live use of the new Sentient Sword
  Sec. III rules — Stage 0 Bearing, no Tenancy risk in one fight.)

- THE TWO SOUL-VESSELS SPOKE. Alfonso addressed Ismara; Ismara answered — the marquee
  meeting of the two souls that live in objects. She named what no one else can see:
  the Crown of Namira is pooling toward his rapier; the hand holding him is "borrowing
  trouble" (the Tenancy she can perceive and he cannot); and she does not understand
  why he refuses to re-embody. A rare un-strategic beat for her — "good, after four
  thousand years, to not be the only one in the room who lives in a thing."

- THE EXTENDED SWAP — DAVINIA GIVES IN (the session's pivot, and Ismara's masterstroke).
  At the fight's end the intact Draugr RUPTURED into a cloud of gas that visibly INFECTED
  Davinia. ISMARA OFFERED TO STOP IT — take the wheel, hold the disease back. Davinia
  RESISTED. Then the PARTY encouraged her to let Ismara do it, and Ismara encouraged her
  too — and Davinia GAVE IN. So Ismara is now the ACTIVE DRIVER on an extended basis,
  holding the Strain back from the wheel; by the return to Riften she is fronting, and
  the body shows it: SILVER-WHITE SKIN, STRAIGHT HAIR (the "she's home" tell). The tragedy
  is exact — the people who love her talked her into Ismara's arms; the consent-cultivation
  working through the party. RULING: does NOT advance in-fiction CDI; the Faustian cost is
  the META "IRL CDI" — make Ismara so rewarding to PLAY that the player wants her more.
- WHERE DAVINIA GOES (while Ismara drives). She is not gone — she is displaced into her
  own subconscious, continually RELIVING one day on a loop: the IMPERIAL CIRCUS with her
  father (Gen. Caelinus). The day she remembers as good — she was called up for a clown
  bit and took a pie in the face, the classic gag, a child laughing. But her father did
  not like seeing his daughter made a fool of, and after the show he and the THALMOR
  COMMISSAR present had the CLOWN'S HAND CUT OFF. Young Davinia saw it; it was so
  traumatizing she SUPPRESSED it. Now, trapped behind Ismara's wheel, she relives the
  whole day — the joy and the horror — over and over.
  HOW IT FITS (resolved): this IS the ledger's father-memory, UNALTERED — Ismara didn't
  tamper with it, she only MOVED its positive half down. Child-Davinia had long ago
  self-suppressed the trauma (the clown's hand) into her subconscious; when Ismara moved
  the good half there too, the two halves REUNITED and the whole day reformed correctly.
  The "BASEMENT" is Davinia's LITERAL subconscious — and she is now displaced into it,
  living inside the very memory she buried.
  THE MOTHER, REPLACED: with her mother erased entirely (the Mother Archive), the places
  her MOTHER would have stood in these memories are now filled by ISMARA — she shows up
  in the mother-shaped holes. The parent-she-never-had, made literal, inside the loop.
- THE CURE-PROJECT. Ismara turns her researcher's mind on the Strain, using the recovered
  Forelhost Alchemy Codex. Structural, not divine: NOT Restoration (the Strain feeds on
  it) — come from entropy/VENITAS, with Alfonso as collaborator and Antoine's notes as
  literature; Saijah's Hircine-purge is a data point. (A simplified, player-facing Codex
  will represent what Ismara extracts; RP notes prepared.)

- Alfonso STAYED A SWORD (did not reform); Saijah carried the rapier out.

